The State Capture report has recommended law enforcement agencies and the NPA to investigate cases of corruption and fraud at SAA, SAA Technical and SA Express. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos brings you more on this. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture report has recommended law enforcement agencies and the National Prosecuting Authority (NPA)  to investigate cases of corruption and fraud at SAA, SAA Technical and SA Express. Justice Raymond Zondo has ordered the NPA to recover lost funds from those who benefited from illegal deals at these airlines. READ: State Capture Inquiry | Good Party urges NPA to act on allegations SA Express was under scrutiny at the state capture inquiry for questionable contracts and suspicious payments. eNCA reporter, Heidi Giokos unpacks this.